{"hero2_chn" "The \"Panzer I B\" is a gift from our earstwhile German friends, complete with German training we can show the enemy that China is not lacking in modern armor support. Remember though, this tank is lightly armored and is best used in a combined shock attack against enemy infantry!"}
{"hero3_chn" "The \"Willys AT\" is a standard jeep with one exception, a double mounted bazooka capable of taking out any tank the enemy can field. With this relativly cheap piece of equipment we can give out boys a fighting chance against superior armor."}
{"hero4_chn" "The \"Guerrilla Uprising\" represents our biggest asset, sheer manpower. Though we can't afford to equip these simple folk with the modern weapons our enemies seem to cherish, their will and weight of number will overcome even the most determined enemy standing before them!"}
{"hero5_chn" "The \"Korean Rebels\" are yet more patriots living under the cruel yoke of the Japanese, let us use them to our advantage. With even more experience fighting the Japanese behind enemy lines we can use them to overcome the enemy through stealth. Equiped by the Chinese government with a varity of SMG's, rifles and anti-tank capabilities, deply these men behind their lines to cause disruption and chaos!"}
{"hero6_chn" "The \"SU-12\" is a small weapon made with simple materials, but with great effectiveness: A typical example of Russian Ingenuity. How we aquired this? No body seems to know but it's a reliable and cheap to maintain SPG. Shoot and scoot or hide behind the hill, it's up to you."}
{"hero7_chn" "The \"Burma Road Soldiers\" are China's answer to the three track jack. Provided to us by the sympathetic British they come equiped with the best small arms China has to offer and transported in a US half track. Strike our foe's with speed at their weak spots."}
{"hero8_chn" "The \"122mm A-19\" is a Soviet field gun developed in late 1930s by combining the barrel of the 122 mm gun M1931 (A-19) and the carriage of the 152 mm howitzer-gun M1937 (ML-20). The gun was in production from 1939 until 1946. It saw action in World War II (primarily with corps and RVGK artillery of the Red Army) and remained in service for a long time after the end of the war. Vehicle-mounted variants of the gun were fitted to the IS-2 and 3 tanks and ISU-122 self-propelled gun. Easily our most powerful anti-tank gun!"}
{"hero9_chn" "The \"Radio Operator\" is a specially trained infantryman capable of calling in precise artillery strikes with his signal flares. A trained artillery observer awaits in the rear, ready at a moments' notice to direct fire down onto any signals he sees. The Radio Operator's unique abilities make him valuable, and special care should be taken to keep him from harm."}
{"hero10_chn" "The \"China Uprising\" is simply the will of the people to stand up and fight against the invador. Armed with an assortment of weapons including rifles and smg's they can be the difference between being pinned back and overwhelming a determined enemy. Essentially this is Guerrilla Uprising on crack."}
{"hero11_chn" "The \"Foreign Aid\" is a little bit of help from our US friends. Trained imported but not vetran crewed Chaffee!!!!! x2. "}
{"hero12_chn" " The \"WZ-111\" The WZ-111 featured a 750 hp supercharged diesel engine and torsion bar suspension system. The idler wheels were in front with drive sprockets in the rear. Many of the suspension components were the same type used in Soviet heavy tank designs such as the IS-2. Imported and trained from the 60s we can use this 20 year advantage on our opponents"}